Thanks for the update. I'm glad the installation was successful, but I'd like point out that manual changes directly during the
installation process are not tested. So we cannot guarantee the system is or will remain 100% healthy, and this is not supported.

I'm reducing the severity and removing the 24x7 flag.

About this:
>>pki-tomcatd startup time — takes 45-60 minutes on every restart due to ~1M certificate entries in o=ipaca. We need guidance on how to purge expired certificates from the CA database to reduce startup time.

I'd strongly suggest you check whether most of these certs are really organic. The JIRA I mentioned is this one both upstream and internal:
---
https://pagure.io/certmonger/pull-request/303
https://redhat.atlassian.net/browse/RHEL-159362
---

And may match the behaviour here in case these 1,089,773 entries are really not being used. rhel-9 has a prune feature but that requires rsnv3,
and your current topology does not support that. You'd need a full fresh install and then migrate the data over.

Considering the 1mi certificates, however, along with the way this replica has been installed in a topology with centOS 7 servers,
that would be the best way ahead to ensure you have a 100% working environment.

